'''Alain Huetz de Lemps''' is a French [[geographer]] and [[botanist]]. He is a lecturer at [[Bordeaux University]] ([[Bordeaux]], France) and Honoris Causa professor of the [[University of Valladolid]] ([[Valladolid]], Spain).<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.universityofvalladolid.uva.es/quality/honoris.html |title=Archived copy |access-date=2009-05-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091215032913/http://www.universityofvalladolid.uva.es/quality/honoris.html |archive-date=2009-12-15 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref> He wrote a primary reference work on wine in [[Castile and León]], ''Vinos y Viñedos de Castilla y León''.<ref>http://www.nortecastilla.es/prensa/20070414/castilla_leon/homenaje-alain-huetz-lemps_20070414.html. (Spanish only)</ref>

He is the author of approximately 20 books and over 100 papers on the subjects of Spain ([[wine]], [[Distilled beverage|spirits]], [[fortified wine]], [[botany]]), wines and spirits in general, [[sugar cane]], and [[Oceania]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.casadevelazquez.org/bibliographie/fhuetz_alain.htm |title=Archived copy |access-date=2009-05-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081115020824/http://www.casadevelazquez.org/bibliographie/fhuetz_alain.htm |archive-date=2008-11-15 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref>

