'''Ambush Bay''' ({{coord|63|10|S|55|26|W|}}) is a [[bay]] 3.5 nautical miles (6 km) wide indenting the north coast of [[Joinville Island]] immediately east of [[King Point]]. Surveyed by the [[Falkland Islands Dependencies Survey]] (FIDS) in 1953. The name arose because the bay is a trap for the unwary if its shallow and foul nature is not known.

